rush
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a place where gold is found, and to which consequently a crowd of diggers `rush.' [1855]


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: goldmining; nb ref to place not process
